#. type: multicols*
#: sections/combat.tex:9
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\pagetarget{Combat}{Combat}\\index{Combat} with \\textbf{Neutral Units} starts when a Hero moves to an \\textbf{unvisited} Field with a roman numeral, signifying the \\hyperlink{Difficulty Table}{type and number} of Neutral Units guarding that Field.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"Un \\pagetarget{Combat}{Combate}\\index{Combate} con \\textbf{Unidades Neutrales} se da cuando un Héroe entra en una Casilla \\textbf{no visitada} con un número romano que indica el \\hyperlink{Difficulty Table}{tipo y número} de Unidades Neutrales en esa Casilla.\n"
"\n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/combat.tex:16
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Combat with \\textbf{another player} can start in two ways:\n"
"\\begin{itemize}\n"
"  \\item You move into any Field containing one of their Heroes.\n"
"  \\item You move into a Town or Settlement owned by them.\n"
"\\end{itemize}\n"
"Players are able to start multiple Combats during their Turn.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"Un Combate contra \\textbf{otro Héroe} puede comenzar de dos maneras:\n"
"\\begin{itemize}\n"
"  \\item Te mueves a cualquier Casilla que contenga uno de sus Héroes.\n"
"  \\item Te mueves a una Ciudad o Asentamiento de su propiedad.\n"
"\\end{itemize}\n"
"Los jugadores pueden iniciar varios combates durante su Turno.\n"
"\n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/combat.tex:18
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "\\note{6}{\n"
#| "  When a \\pagelink{Secondary}{Secondary Hero} is attacked, they \\textbf{may choose} to be \\pagelink{Endcombat}{instantly defeated} instead of engaging in Combat, which helps to preserve the Units.\n"
#| "}\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"When a \\pagelink{Secondary}{Secondary Hero} is attacked, they \\textbf{may choose} to be \\pagelink{Endcombat}{instantly defeated} instead of engaging in Combat, which helps to preserve the Units.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\\note{6}{\n"
"Cuando un \\pagelink{Secondary}{Héroe Secundario} es atacado \\textbf{puede elegir} ser \\pagelink{Endcombat}{derrotado instantáneamente} en lugar de Combatir para preservar sus Unidades.\n"
"}\n"
"\n"

